<h3>Codebase &amp; Colophon</h3>
   <p></p>

   <p>OHinAA was originally authored in <%= link_to "Ruby on Rails", 'http://rubyonrails.org/' %> (Ruby 3.2.8 with Rails 1.9.3).</p>

   <p>The nuts and bolts are based loosely on the fan<em>tabulous</em> <%= link_to "RailsTutorial", 'http://railstutorial.org' %>.</p>

   <p>For now, the site is supported by ads. It's not free to build, host and maintain this stuff.  But remember:  sobriety <em>is</em> free.  .  .  ;) </p>

   <p>This lovely design has been <%= link_to "custom created by HCS", 'http://www.hackeress.com' %>. Background image by <%= link_to "SkyBlue2U", 'http://www.colourlovers.com/pattern/2525598/Conchos_Leather' %>.   

   <p>Hosting is on <%= link_to "Linode", 'http://www.linode.com/?r=e4c15a5a5b91a8cd10bdb9e5df989a2c373c3aeb' %>, which rocks as much as a webhost can rock (And while we're on the subject: for the love of God, never ever use GoDaddy!).</p>

   <p>The entire codebase is <%= link_to "hosted on Github", 'http://github.com/indie/serenity' %>, so feel free to fork, contribute, and issue pull requests for new features.</p>
               
